-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--  Migration Notes
--
--  The application code (db.js) uses ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN statements
--  wrapped in try/catch to add columns to existing databases. These
--  migrations run AFTER the initial CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS and index
--  creation.
--
--  Two indexes are created AFTER migrations because they reference
--  migration-added columns:
--    idx_gateways_active_mode  → depends on 'mode' column   (gateways)
--    idx_inbound_agent_id       → depends on 'agent_id' column (inbound)
--
--  All other indexes reference columns that exist in the original
--  CREATE TABLE statements and are safe to create up front.
-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
